<P><H1 align=center>OTHER DETAILS FOR EMPLOYED PERIOD – DC181</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>areas shown in 
red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>            </P>
<P><H3>Last 3 Wage Slips Seen? / P60 Seen?: </H3>these may be 
required in addition or as an alternative to an employer’s reference, as they 
will corroborate the applicant’s income and tax details. Select the ‘Yes’ radio 
button if these have been viewed
<P></P>
<P><H3>Notice of Termination or Redundancy?: </H3>if the 
applicant is aware of any impending termination of this employment or 
redundancy, this should be advised as it may have a negative impact on the 
application (depending on the <A href="HELP_MC010.asp#LendingCriteria">lending criteria</A>)
<P></P>
<P><H3>Own 5% or more of shares in Company?: </H3>Required as 
part of income details to assess whether the applicant is just an employee, or 
alternatively a part owner of the company, as different lending criteria may 
apply to these situations.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Subject to probationary period?: </H3>If applicant has 
recently started a new job, they may be subject to a probationary period before 
employment is deemed permanent. This information helps to assess the stability 
of the employment.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Related to employer?: </H3>Some lenders may consider 
this a risk to permanent employment.
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>clicking on OK leads to the next screen.
<P></P>
